Essential test results BRH
Choice of the award procedure
The audited contracting authorities largely wrote out the construction work in an open procedure or in a public invitation to tender and thus complied with the budgetary and procurement regulations.
In 2011, 59.5% of federal building construction work was publicly advertised or open-ended.
In road construction, this share was 94.8%.
The choice of non-public procurement methods lacked in-depth reasons why the contracting entities had to depart from the open procedure or public tender procedure.
