If a tenderer submits a petition for review within the information period, a contract can only be concluded after the final decision in the review procedure.
In addition, companies may have the award decision reviewed by an independent court during this review procedure.
The review procedure is intended to ensure the legal protection of companies and to oblige the client throughout the procurement procedure to observe the procurement law.
For this he must document the procedure sufficiently.
Regulations of the German and Czech public procurement law
Same or similar regulations
Both countries have implemented the EU rules on information and review procedures.
In both countries, the contracting authority must decide on the award.
However, it must not deviate arbitrarily from the result of a proper examination and evaluation of the offers.
The client should place the order within the announced additional period,
also because the bidders are no longer bound to their offers after the deadline.
In the case of open and non-open procedures or public and restricted tenders, the client may not in principle deviate from the offer contents when signing the contract.
The unsuccessful tenderers shall be informed promptly of the award decision and of the reasons for not considering their tenders.
Award procedures may only be suspended under certain conditions, eg. For example, if the bid prices are excessive or the bids do not meet the requirements of the call for bids.
Divergent regulations
In the Czech Republic, the 10- and 15-day information and waiting obligations prior to the award of the contract also apply to works not available throughout Europe.
In Germany, these requirements apply only to the area of EU-wide awards.
For the other procedures in Germany tenderers may be informed of the award decision only after the award of the contract.
In the Czech Republic, a tendering procedure should be canceled if only one tender has been received or only one bid has been accepted.
In Germany, the surcharge is also awarded in the case of only one value-added offer, provided that it meets the conditions of the tender and is economical.
Essential test results
BRH
In the case of the audited contracts, there were only a few complaints when concluding the award procedure.
In some cases, companies have already received an order for an EU-wide contract prior to the expiry of the information period, which may result in the ineffectiveness of the contract.
In addition, order letters contained open-ended procedures in individual cases that deviated from the content of the offer, such as: Eg changed dates.
In several cases, the contracting authorities did not comply with the additional periods.
In the case of an open procedure, therefore, one contracting authority awarded the second lowest bid, since an undertaking offering a discount of 50% would no longer be prepared, at the end of the additional period, to perform the services at the price originally offered.
